Task:
Create or update tests for the specified code change.

Todo:
- Title: {{ todo_title | default('Test creation task') }}
- Description: {{ todo_description | default('Create tests that verify the expected behavior.') }}
- Work type: {{ work_type | default('test') }}
- Queue: {{ queue | default('qa') }}
- Priority: {{ priority | default('medium') }}

Instructions:
1. Identify the behavior that needs to be tested.
2. Write unit tests first (>85% line coverage per file).
3. Write integration tests covering 2+ subsystem interaction.
4. Write E2E tests if the change has user-facing impact.
5. Write Molecule scenarios for any Ansible playbooks, roles, or tool wrappers.
6. Verify tests FAIL before implementation, PASS after.
7. Verify coverage meets the configured threshold.

Test quality requirements:
- Each test must have Arrange-Act-Assert structure.
- Test names must describe the behavior: test_<subject>_<condition>_<expected>.
- Include positive and negative cases.
- Test edge cases (empty input, invalid input, boundary values).
- Test error paths and fallback behavior.
- Use realistic test data, not placeholders.

Molecule requirements for Ansible content:
- Scenario must call the real playbook/role/wrapper.
- Verify must use explicit assert tasks with fail_msg.
- Include idempotence check for idempotent content.
- Include at least one negative-path scenario.
